### 1. **Scikit-learn Documentation (Classification & Evaluation)**
- **Classification metrics**: Precision, Recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC  
  Scikit-learn Classification Metrics Guide [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fmodel_evaluation.html%23classification-metrics")  
- **Class weights**: Handling imbalanced datasets by adjusting weights in classifiers  
  Scikit-learn Class Weight Parameter [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fgenerated%2Fsklearn.linear_model.LogisticRegression.html")  

### 2. **Imbalanced-learn (imblearn) Library**
- Provides advanced tools for handling imbalanced datasets (oversampling, undersampling, SMOTE).  
- Documentation: Imbalanced-learn User Guide [(imbalanced-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fimbalanced-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fuser_guide.html")  

### 3. **Credit Risk Prediction Projects**
- Example GitHub project: *Credit Risk Prediction System using Scikit-learn*  
  Shows how supervised learning algorithms can classify loan applicants as likely to default.  
  GitHub Project: Credit Risk Prediction ML [(github.com in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2FBhuvana5c3%2FCredit-risk-prediction-ML")  

### 4. **Credit Risk Modeling in Finance**
- Documentation of probability-of-default (PD) scoring models using Scikit-learn.  
- Grounded in Basel II/III regulatory frameworks for credit risk quantification.  
  Credit Risk Modeling Resources [(deepwiki.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fdeepwiki.org%2Fwiki%2FCredit_Risk_Modeling")  

